.TH ID "1" "April 2026" "GNU coreutils 9.11" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
id \- print real and effective user and group IDs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B id
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR]... [\fI\,USER\/\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.\" Add any additional description here
.PP
Print user and group information for each specified USER,
or (when USER omitted) for the current process.
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#id-a'\fB\-a\fP\X'tty: link'
ignore, for compatibility with other versions
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#id-Z'\fB\-Z, \-\-context\fP\X'tty: link'
print only the security context of the process
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#id-g'\fB\-g, \-\-group\fP\X'tty: link'
print only the effective group ID
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#id-G'\fB\-G, \-\-groups\fP\X'tty: link'
print all group IDs
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#id-n'\fB\-n, \-\-name\fP\X'tty: link'
print a name instead of a number, for \fB\-u\fR,\-g,\-G
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#id-r'\fB\-r, \-\-real\fP\X'tty: link'
print the real ID instead of the effective ID, with \fB\-u\fR,\-g,\-G
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#id-u'\fB\-u, \-\-user\fP\X'tty: link'
print only the effective user ID
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#id-z'\fB\-z, \-\-zero\fP\X'tty: link'
delimit entries with NUL characters, not whitespace;
not permitted in default format
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/id#id--help'\fB\-\-help\fP\X'tty: link'
display this help and exit
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/id#id--version'\fB\-\-version\fP\X'tty: link'
output version information and exit
.PP
Without any OPTION, print some useful set of identified information.
